text: Christ spoiler season is long this time around...
It's barely stopped for four seasons
Yeah, but we're back to 2 weeks or so...

All right, thoughts before we move on to drinking from the Eldraine firehose:

• <@U3QMCLQQG>, I've actually loved C19. The Precon tournament was a blast despite Wizards trying to ruin it, and getting underloved mechanics some direct love was a great idea that will be appreciated in the long run.
• The Commander Product now _has_ to be the specific product, due to Brawl. I've gone into this a couple times, but the basic problem is that the card pool of brawl is so small that any given commander may be the only option in that color combination, and as such has to be very broad. This means that the category of "broad" commander is always going to be taken up by the new standard products, leaving less room for more of the same in Commander/Modern/BBD products.
• All that said, I'm not sure why people aren't loving the new commanders, outside of the hipster feel that a lot of us have when it comes to being spoonfed by the precons. Kriik is some nice spice for the spikes out there, Anje is feeding cEDH while ultimately being a fun "i'm doing a lot of things" kind of commander in a color combination that didn't have much of that, Gerrard brought aristocrats to Boros while providing a non-combat means of card advantage and got no credit for it, Sevinne is interesting even just outside of the Flashback territory, and Pramikon and Atla Palani are both great memes for meme builders that could also be made to be a bit mean with the right kind of ingenuity. Oh, and Volrath, Chainer, and Greven are just interesting and powerful. There's avenues for almost every single one of these guys, but we as a community seem to be moving the bar ever higher to keep ourselves disillusioned.
• Reprints... I've just never understood this complaint. Maybe people are thinking of all the new CMDR cards that have since become expensive and lumping those in, but what was the last big reprint you remember in a commander product? It's not really what its for, and the product always ends up worth more than you paid for it. What exactly *is* the complaint?
• New stuff: From any commander product, you're gonna get a handful of cards that become played in large numbers. In my opinion, this is a success when those cards feed specific decks, rather than just being the new staple for a color. Teferi's Protection is a great example of this. It's become a $30+ chase card that is just an auto-play in any white deck that the owner can afford, and that's not what you should be looking for from a commander product. On the other hand, Bone Miser, Sevinne's Reclamation, Dockside Extortionist, Ohran Frostfang, and Gift of Doom all pretty much hit the nail on the head when it comes to playability without straying into "every deck has to play this now" territory.

It's not the best commander product ever (although I will bring up that the one that's widely lauded as the best created more problems for the format than any product ever has), but it's got a lot going for it, and at least in my opinion, it's fun. Can we stop acting like Wizards screwed up here?
Anje is NOT fun. It’s a fifteen min durdle turn Commander. Have you seen a non-stock Anje deck?
I don't disagree, Dana, but people like fifteen minute durdle turn Commanders. That's why a third of the top commanders are 15 minute durdle turn commanders.
Again, "I'm doing a lot of things" is exciting for the person doing it, and hasn't really been an available option in Rakdos, at least not in this direct a fashion.
<@U3L7A68JC> spoiler season for Eldraine is the same length as all the standard sets have been this year. ~Week and a half.
I know...but after the last few being so accelerated it just feels long now.
Remember when it used to be 3 weeks? :joy:

I do like a lot of the Commanders from c19. I think most of them are interesting in some way. Their biggest problem was people don't get hyped for a lot of $2 reprints that save the card from going up to $4. They want the $15 reprints.
The meme around here was that all the reprints were exactly $6, but I take your point. They're not exciting reprints.

I don't buy that the Brawl commanders are broad to make it easier though. I think they're easy-mode strong cards designed to make lazy players who want to just sit and pub stomp buy decks to use in Commander. I reject the notion that someone looked at Chulane, Korvold or Alela and thought they did a great job creating decks that led to interesting gameplay.
The brawl commanders are designed with the same corporate mindset that puts R&D into making cigarettes more addictive.
The main concern was increasing sales.
I don't disagree with that, either. I do wish that R&D would actually look at slowing down their power creep, which has become more of a power sprint.
the new esper faerie kind of made me triggered because it's basically better Sai

The brawl commanders also probably HAVE to be a little more powerful considering they're designed for brawl where the average card power level is significantly lower than edh. They have to make the brawl legendaries a little pushed to keep the gameplay moving and people to stay interested. That does lend itself to making pretty much any good commander KOS though
